  "response": "The shortest completed Test match in terms of the number of balls bowled is the **England vs. West Indies** match that took place at **North Sound, Antigua** on **January 12\u201313, 2009**. This match lasted just **30.2 overs** (182 balls) before being abandoned due to an unfit playing surface.\n\nThe pitch was deemed dangerous and unplayable, with the match being called off as a **draw** after just over a day's play. No official result was achieved, making it the shortest completed Test match in history in terms of playing time. \n\nHowever, if considering matches that reached a result, the shortest completed Test match is the **England vs. Australia** match at **Lord's, London** in **1888**, which lasted **656 balls** over two days.\n\nSo, the answer depends on whether you include abandoned matches or only those that reached a result:\n\n- **Shortest completed Test (abandoned):** England vs. West Indies (2009) \u2013 **30.2 overs** (182 balls).\n- **Shortest completed Test (with a result):** England vs. Australia (1888) \u2013 **656 balls**.",
